    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-07-02T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-07-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="429" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d429">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Uhl</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Dupuy de Lôme</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-07-02">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 2,
                                1895</hi>.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The Acting Secretary of State presents his compliments to the Spanish
                            minister and has the honor to acknowledge, with thanks, the receipt of
                            the minister’s note of the 1st instant, with which is inclosed an
                            account of the sitting held by the Spanish Senate on the 15th ultimo, at
                            which sitting the Government was questioned by Señor Ortiz de Pinedo,
                            senator for the Island of Cuba, as to the observance by the United
                            States of its neutrality laws.</p>
                <p>The Acting Secretary of State has read with pleasure the deserved tribute
                            paid by the Duke of Tetuan to the impartial friendliness of this
                            Government.</p>
            </div>
